# research_data desk — always-on rules

This repo is a **personal US stocks/ETFs research desk** (`research_data`). Folder name `tradingview` is historical only — not affiliated with TradingView.com.

## Settled product law
- Personal-only; never sold; no auth/tenancy.
- Stocks/ETFs only. Zero Kalshi/Polymarket/PM code or schema.
- Python owns facts/factors/tests/paper fills. AI proposes/explains from evidence only — never invents numbers.
- Action vocabulary only: `WATCH | HOLD | ACCUMULATE | REDUCE | AVOID | INSUFFICIENT_DATA`.
- No execution language: `BUY`, `SELL`, "guaranteed", "risk-free" (except guardrail enforcement strings that assert against those tokens).
- Four gates fixed order: OOS → Monte Carlo → walk-forward → deflated Sharpe. Literature defaults. Never loosen to force a live pass.
- Kronos: `kronos_reserved.py` only — no inference until RankIC validation session.
- Human approver identity: `anant`.
- Universe locked at 14 symbols (`BRKB` letters-only).

## Engineering law
- Offline CI only: no network in pytest. Live scripts under `scripts/` are separate.
- Branch off `main` → PR → green CI. See `Docs/GITHUB_WORKFLOW.md`.
- Do not redesign working ingestion spine drive-by; fix only real bugs hit by the current slice.
- Vault SoT: `Session Findings — Post Base (2026-07-11)` when present, else `Session Findings — Cursor Alignment Pass (2026-07-10)`.
- Architecture mirror: `Docs/YEAR_AHEAD_BASE.md`. Phase 2 pack: `Docs/PHASE2_STRATEGY_PACK.md`. History depth: `Docs/HISTORY_DEPTH.md`.

## Before claiming done
- Run `pytest -q` offline.
- Ground progress claims in tool output from this session.
- Prefer smallest diff that fully solves the task.
